*There was a waylay in France along the way, is that right?*

*DK:* Yes. We used to go to France for the summer, so at the time no one re=
ally knew the changes afoot in Iran. So we thought that we would just leave=
, go to France while things cooled down, calmed down so to speak. And they =
never did calm down.

*Right. Arguably still haven't.*

*DK:* And yeah, I'm arguably still on vacation in France.

So the vacation has continued, but we were lucky enough to come to the Stat=
es and rebuild our lives. And then I had the average suburban childhood. I =
studied engineering in college, and quickly through that all the way to sta=
rt a career in New York and finance, working at investment bank, Allen & Co=
mpany, that you might know, which is a great place. And then, one thing led=
